===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|pere}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|pere}}, common North and West Germanic, from {{etyl|VL.|en}} {{m|la|*pira}}, originally the plural of {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|pirum}} but reconstrued as a feminine singular. Cognate with {{cog|stq|Peere||pear}}, Dutch {{m|nl|peer||pear}}, Danish {{m|da|pære||pear}}, Swedish {{m|sv|päron||pear}}, Icelandic {{m|is|pera||pear}}.

